NV </a><a href="/solar-henderson-nv" class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-solar-cream border border-slate-200 hover:border-brand-orange rounded-xl px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 hover:text-brand-orange transition-all duration-200 group"> <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-slate-400 group-hover:text-brand-orange" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0118 0z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"></circle></svg> Henderson, NV </a><a href="/solar-north-las-vegas" class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-solar-cream border border-slate-200 hover:border-brand-orange rounded-xl px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 hover:text-brand-orange transition-all duration-200 group"> <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-slate-400 group-hover:text-brand-orange" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0118 0z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"></circle></svg> North Las Vegas, NV </a><a href="/solar-los-angeles" class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-solar-cream border border-slate-200 hover:border-brand-orange rounded-xl px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 hover:text-brand-orange transition-all duration-200 group"> <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-slate-400 group-hover:text-brand-orange" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0118 0z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"></circle></svg> Los Angeles, CA </a><a href="/solar-san-diego" class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-solar-cream border border-slate-200 hover:border-brand-orange rounded-xl px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 hover:text-brand-orange transition-all duration-200 group"> <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-slate-400 group-hover:text-brand-orange" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0118 0z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"></circle></svg> San Diego, CA </a><a href="/solar-riverside" class="flex items-center gap-2 bg-slate-50 hover:bg-solar-cream border border-slate-200 hover:border-brand-orange rounded-xl px-4 py-3 text-sm font-medium text-slate-700 hover:text-brand-orange transition-all duration-200 group"> <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="text-slate-400 group-hover:text-brand-orange" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M21 10c0 7-9 13-9 13s-9-6-9-13a9 9 0 0118 0z"></path><circle cx="12" cy="10" r="3"></circle></svg> Riverside, CA </a> </div> </div> </section>  <script type="application/ld+json">{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"How much does solar cost in Las Vegas?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most Las Vegas homeowners go solar for $0 down with financing. The average system size is 6–8kW, costing $15,000–$22,000 before incentives. After the 30% federal tax credit, your net cost drops to $10,500–$15,400. Monthly savings typically range from $150–$400 depending on your current NV Energy bill."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the 30% federal solar tax credit?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The Inflation Reduction Act provides a 30% Investment Tax Credit (ITC) on the full cost of your solar installation. If your system costs $18,000, you receive a $5,400 credit directly off your federal taxes. This credit is available through at least 2032 but may be subject to future legislative changes."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How does NV Energy net metering work?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"NV Energy's net metering program lets you sell excess solar energy back to the grid. When your panels produce more than you use, the surplus spins your meter backward. You receive a credit at a retail rate, which offsets the energy you pull from the grid at night. This significantly reduces or eliminates your electric bill."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Is Daniel Hadobas a licensed solar contractor?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Daniel is a licensed solar energy specialist and independent agent with Sunder Energy, one of the nation's top-rated residential solar companies. He handles permitting, HOA approvals, utility interconnection, and monitors your system post-install to ensure everything performs as promised."}}]}</script> <section class="py-16 px-4"> <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto"> <div class="text-center mb-10"> <div class="section-divider mx-auto mb-4"></div> <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-brand-dark">Solar FAQs for Las Vegas Homeowners</h2> </div> <div class="space-y-3"> <details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-100 shadow-sm overflow-hidden"> <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 cursor-pointer px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-brand-dark hover:text-brand-orange transition-colors list-none" aria-expanded="false"> <span class="flex items-start gap-3"> <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-brand-orange/10 text-brand-orange text-xs font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5"> 1 </span> How much does solar cost in Las Vegas? </span> <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"> <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path> </svg> </summary> <div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-1 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-sm border-t border-slate-50"> Most Las Vegas homeowners go solar for $0 down with financing. The average system size is 6–8kW, costing $15,000–$22,000 before incentives. After the 30% federal tax credit, your net cost drops to $10,500–$15,400. Monthly savings typically range from $150–$400 depending on your current NV Energy bill. </div> </details><details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-100 shadow-sm overflow-hidden"> <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 cursor-pointer px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-brand-dark hover:text-brand-orange transition-colors list-none" aria-expanded="false"> <span class="flex items-start gap-3"> <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-brand-orange/10 text-brand-orange text-xs font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5"> 2 </span> What is the 30% federal solar tax credit? </span> <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"> <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path> </svg> </summary> <div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-1 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-sm border-t border-slate-50"> The Inflation Reduction Act provides a 30% Investment Tax Credit (ITC) on the full cost of your solar installation. If your system costs $18,000, you receive a $5,400 credit directly off your federal taxes. This credit is available through at least 2032 but may be subject to future legislative changes. </div> </details><details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-100 shadow-sm overflow-hidden"> <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 cursor-pointer px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-brand-dark hover:text-brand-orange transition-colors list-none" aria-expanded="false"> <span class="flex items-start gap-3"> <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-brand-orange/10 text-brand-orange text-xs font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5"> 3 </span> How does NV Energy net metering work? </span> <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"> <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path> </svg> </summary> <div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-1 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-sm border-t border-slate-50"> NV Energy&#39;s net metering program lets you sell excess solar energy back to the grid. When your panels produce more than you use, the surplus spins your meter backward. You receive a credit at a retail rate, which offsets the energy you pull from the grid at night. This significantly reduces or eliminates your electric bill. </div> </details><details class="group bg-white rounded-xl border border-slate-100 shadow-sm overflow-hidden"> <summary class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 cursor-pointer px-6 py-4 font-semibold text-brand-dark hover:text-brand-orange transition-colors list-none" aria-expanded="false"> <span class="flex items-start gap-3"> <span class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-6 h-6 rounded-full bg-brand-orange/10 text-brand-orange text-xs font-bold shrink-0 mt-0.5"> 4 </span> Is Daniel Hadobas a licensed solar contractor? </span> <svg class="w-5 h-5 shrink-0 text-slate-400 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform duration-200" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"> <path d="M6 9l6 6 6-6"></path> </svg> </summary> <div class="px-6 pb-5 pt-1 text-slate-600 leading-relaxed text-sm border-t border-slate-50"> Daniel is a licensed solar energy specialist and independent agent with Sunder Energy, one of the nation&#39;s top-rated residential solar companies. He handles permitting, HOA approvals, utility interconnection, and monitors your system post-install to ensure everything performs as promised. </div> </details> </div> </div> </section>  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-brand-dark to-slate-800 py-20 px-4"> <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center"> <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-brand-orange/20 border border-brand-orange/30 text-brand-orange rounded-full px-4 py-1.5 text-xs font-semibold mb-6">
